## Architecture Decision Records (ADR)

### Purpose

ADRs document significant decisions: why a particular approach was chosen, what alternatives were considered, and what was rejected.

### Format

```markdown
# ADR-0001: Discord bot is a client adapter only

## Status
Accepted

## Context
We need to decide how to structure the application so that:
1. Game logic is testable without Discord
2. A future web client can reuse game logic
3. The bot doesn't become a tangled mess of business logic

## Decision
The Discord bot will be a pure UI adapter. It receives interactions,
calls the API, and renders responses. All game logic lives in
packages/core as pure TypeScript functions.

## Consequences
Positive:
- Game logic is completely testable
- Web client can reuse core
- Bot stays simple

Negative:
- Every bot action requires an API call
- Latency between interaction and response
- More infrastructure required

## Alternatives Considered

### Bot contains game logic directly
Rejected: Would require rewriting game logic for web client.
Would make unit testing impossible.

### Bot imports core directly (no API)
Partially rejected: API provides better audit trail and
allows admin panel to call same logic. Simpler initially
but less flexible.

---

## Naming Conventions for ADRs

```
ADR-NNNN-title-in-kebab-case.md
```

Numbering starts at 0001 and increments.

---

## Documentation Update Triggers

| Trigger | Required Update |
|---------|----------------|
| New realm added | `docs/realms.md`, `kb/canon/cultivation-realms.md` |
| New region added | `docs/regions.md`, `kb/canon/regions.md` |
| New sect added | `docs/world-bible.md`, `kb/canon/sects.md` |
| Balance change | `docs/game-balancing.md`, `docs/rules.md` |
| New API endpoint | `kb/engineering/architecture.md` |
| Architecture change | New ADR in `kb/adr/` |
| Lore expansion | `kb/canon/` (no `docs/` unless canon) |

---

## Documentation Review

Before each release:

- [ ] `docs/` matches current game behavior
- [ ] `kb/` is internally consistent
- [ ] No contradictions between `docs/` and `kb/`
- [ ] ADRs are accurate (if approach changed, update ADR consequences)
- [ ] README.md quick start is accurate
- [ ] Cursor rules match current architecture

